external_knowledge:
- A user is considered to have "more than a few creations" if they have created more than one static model;
- "Several tests" refers to more than one test on the date '2023-02-10';
- The activity level of users is determined by the counts of their models and tests, with higher counts indicating higher activity;
- "Compared to others" implies ranking users based on their counts of models and tests.

sql:
SELECT models.model_name, collision_tests.test_date
FROM models
INNER JOIN collision_tests ON models.model_id = collision_tests.model_id;

SELECT at.algorithm_name, pm.execution_time, pm.memory_usage
FROM algorithm_types at
LEFT JOIN performance_metrics pm ON at.algorithm_id = pm.algorithm_id;

SELECT model_name, created_date
FROM models
WHERE author_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(test_id)
FROM collision_tests
WHERE test_date LIKE '2023-02-%';
